![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578252139492-C40E0VCNBQ7PCB10I4TX/image-asset.jpeg)

Slammed by critics, ignored by movie-goers, and laughed at by professionals, Hellboy 2019 is a mix bag at best but is it truly the worst comic book movie ever made? The guys Comicbook Clique review the reboot that has been being kicked around since its release. Gone is Guillermo Tel Toro, Ron Perlman, & John Hurt in exchange for director Neil Marshall, Stranger Things' star David Harbour and veteran actor Ian McShane, in this bloody, retread of the Hellboy mythos. With Mike Mignola (the character's creator) on set helping craft the story what the HELL could go wrong?

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
